# AfterAI Platform rule

Every AfterArtificial Life Domain / Industry Domain module uses **`after_ai`**
— never a parallel AI stack. There is **one assistant**; products extend it
with domain skills only.

## Product responsibility

- Choose an `AfterAiProfile` (or build a domain-specific enable set).
- Register domain **tools / skills / KB content** in the product repo.
- Pass `AfterEcosystemAiContext` so Mate understands the whole Life Domain graph.
- Bridge `OnlineAi` to `after_core` BYOK when shipping cloud Mate.

## Platform responsibility (`packages/after_ai`)

Conversation · Vision · OCR · STT · TTS · Translation · Recommendation · Prediction · Summarization · Semantic Search · Knowledge Base · Automation · Decision Support · Notifications · Workflow Suggestions · Context Memory · Offline AI · Online AI · Prompt Templates · Tool Calling · Plugins.

## Fail closed

Calling a disabled capability throws `AfterAiCapabilityDisabledException`.

